In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims May as Older Americans Month, a tradition that has been upheld for the past 50 years. The article highlights the accomplishments of older Americans and acknowledges their contribution to society. It emphasizes the importance of providing support, appreciation, and dignity to seniors. The Obama Administration is working on various initiatives to help seniors get involved in volunteer service, improve access to healthcare, and broaden employment opportunities. The administration also aims to protect and strengthen Medicare and Social Security for current and future generations. The article concludes by urging all Americans to acknowledge and honor the contributions of older Americans not just during this month but throughout the year.